05/06/2007
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- Macedonian Foreign Minister Antonio Milososki was in Brussels on Monday (June 4th) for a speech to the European Parliament's (EP) Committee on Foreign Affairs. 
He presented the government's achievements in fighting corruption and organised crime and briefed members on the implementation of economic reforms. 
For their part, EP members asked about the name dispute with Greece, the pace of judicial reforms and establishment of Macedonia's Judicial Council.
In other news Monday, Bosnia and Herzegovina Minister of Security Tarik Sadovic was in Bucharest, where he signed a bilateral agreement on police co-operation. 
The accord aims to co-ordinate efforts in fighting terrorism and organised crime. 
(MAkfax, MRT, A1 TV, Fena - 04/06/07)
